## Event Timing

Campaign Events run for **14 days** and typically return every **5 weeks**, allowing players to continue progress across multiple appearances.

## One-Time Path Choice

At the start of each event, you must choose **one path** to pursue.

* You cannot switch paths once selected.
* Your choice remains locked until the event returns.

## Required Characters

Each path is built around **three Required Characters**.

* These characters are needed to access and progress through that path's stages.
* Different paths feature different character requirements.

## Borrowing Characters (Normal Difficulty)

Normal difficulty allows players to borrow Required Characters they do not own.

* Any Required Character can be borrowed.
* Borrowed characters scale up to the stage's maximum Rarity Cap.
* This makes Normal difficulty accessible even for newer accounts.

## Extremis Difficulty

Extremis difficulty removes the borrowing system entirely.

* You must use your own roster.
* Borrowed characters are not available.
* Success depends on how much you've invested in the Required Characters and supporting team members.

For many players, Extremis is where roster depth and long-term planning become most important.

`}
